@startuml Registration Check Flow

title Use Case 1 - Registration Check for a New Naming

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true

actor Lawyer
participant "REST API" as API
participant "Text Check Service" as TextService
participant "Naming Preprocessing" as Preprocess
participant "Embedding Model" as Model
participant "Embedding Dataset" as Dataset
participant "Search Indexes" as Indexes
database "Trademark DB" as DB
database "External Source Store" as External
participant "Similarity Engine" as Similarity
participant "Ranking Engine" as Ranking

Lawyer -> API: Submit naming + Nice classes
API -> API: Validate request
API -> TextService: Start registration check

TextService -> Preprocess: Normalize input naming
Preprocess --> TextService: Canonical naming

TextService -> DB: Filter candidates by Nice classes
DB --> TextService: Candidate ids from trademark DB

par Semantic search
  TextService -> Model: Generate embedding for input naming
  Model --> TextService: Query embedding
  TextService -> Dataset: Find nearest semantic candidates
  Dataset --> TextService: Semantic shortlist
else Phonetic and text search
  TextService -> Indexes: Search by phonetic and text keys
  Indexes --> TextService: Phonetic/text shortlist
else External channels
  TextService -> External: Search prepared external sources
  External --> TextService: External shortlist
end

TextService -> TextService: Merge candidate pools

loop For each candidate
  TextService -> Similarity: Calculate detailed similarity features
  Similarity --> TextService: Semantic, phonetic,\ntext, graphic and legal features
end

TextService -> Ranking: Build final similarity percentage\nand sort results
Ranking --> TextService: Top-200 ranked conflicts

TextService --> API: Registration check result
API --> Lawyer: Conflict list + similarity percentages

@enduml

@startuml Text Infringement Check Flow

title Use Case 2 - Text Infringement Check

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true

actor Lawyer
participant "REST API" as API
participant "Text Check Service" as TextService
participant "Naming Preprocessing" as Preprocess
participant "Similarity Engine" as Similarity

Lawyer -> API: Submit protected naming\n+ suspicious naming
API -> API: Validate request
API -> TextService: Start text infringement check

TextService -> Preprocess: Normalize protected naming
Preprocess --> TextService: Canonical protected naming

TextService -> Preprocess: Normalize suspicious naming
Preprocess --> TextService: Canonical suspicious naming

TextService -> Similarity: Compare the two namings
Similarity --> TextService: Detailed similarity scores\n+ final similarity percentage

TextService --> API: Pairwise comparison result
API --> Lawyer: Similarity percentage\n+ explanation of matches

@enduml

@startuml Logo Comparison Flow

title Use Case 3 - Logo Infringement Check (Optional)

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true

actor Lawyer
participant "REST API" as API
participant "Logo Check Service" as LogoService
participant "Logo Preprocessing" as LogoPreprocess
participant "Logo Feature Extractor" as FeatureExtractor
participant "Visual Similarity Engine" as VisualSimilarity

Lawyer -> API: Submit reference logo\n+ suspicious logo
API -> API: Validate request
API -> LogoService: Start logo comparison

LogoService -> LogoPreprocess: Normalize both logo files
LogoPreprocess --> LogoService: Prepared visual inputs

LogoService -> FeatureExtractor: Extract visual features\nand text-inside-logo if available
FeatureExtractor --> LogoService: Feature vectors

LogoService -> VisualSimilarity: Compare logos
VisualSimilarity --> LogoService: Visual similarity\n+ final similarity percentage

LogoService --> API: Logo comparison result
API --> Lawyer: Similarity percentage\n+ visual comparison summary

@enduml

@startuml Offline Data Preparation Flow

title Use Case 4 - Offline Data Collection and Preparation

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "Scheduler" as Scheduler
participant "Offline Source Collector" as Collector
database "Trademark DB" as DB
participant "External Sources" as Sources
participant "Raw Staging" as Staging
participant "Naming Preprocessing" as Preprocess
participant "Embedding Model" as Model
participant "Search Index Builder" as IndexBuilder
database "Preprocessed Naming Store" as Preprocessed
database "Embedding Dataset" as Dataset
database "Search Indexes" as Indexes
database "External Source Store" as External

Scheduler -> Collector: Start scheduled update

Collector -> DB: Read latest trademark records
DB --> Collector: Trademark raw data

Collector -> Sources: Fetch external source data
Sources --> Collector: Raw external records

Collector -> Staging: Save raw data snapshot

Collector -> Preprocess: Clean and normalize raw namings
Preprocess --> Collector: Canonical namings\n+ removable elements removed

Collector -> Preprocessed: Save prepared namings

Collector -> Model: Generate embeddings for prepared namings
Model --> Collector: Embedding vectors
Collector -> Dataset: Save or refresh embedding dataset

Collector -> IndexBuilder: Build phonetic, text\nand vector indexes
IndexBuilder --> Collector: Fresh indexes
Collector -> Indexes: Publish new indexes

Collector -> External: Save prepared external source names

Collector --> Scheduler: Update completed

@enduml

